Durban - Irate parents continued to protest outside Assegai Primary School on Thursday following grievances over the selection of a new principal. Learning has been disrupted for a 10th day. They are unhappy about the Department of Education’s choice for a new principal at the school. The department has appointed Sharon Ndlovu, a high school teacher, to take over the reigns but parents are up in arms. Read: Parents shut down school over principal's appointment. They believe that Odette Abrahams, who has been acting principal at the school for the last two years, should have been selected.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
